The paper discusses algorithms for computing geodesic paths and distances on three-dimensional surfaces, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and identifies open problems related to data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.SI).
